description: Get information about a dedicated IP address, including the name of the dedicated IP pool that it's associated with, as well information about the automatic warm-up process for the address.

parameters.name: Ip
parameters.description: The IP address that you want to obtain more information about. The value you specify has to be a dedicated IP address that's assocaited with your Amazon Pinpoint account.

nested_items.name: DedicatedIp
nested_items.description: An object that contains information about a dedicated IP address.

nested_items.name: Ip
nested_items.description: An IP address that is reserved for use by your Amazon Pinpoint account.

nested_items.name: WarmupStatus
nested_items.description: The warm-up status of a dedicated IP address. The status can have one of the following values:
IN_PROGRESS --- The IP address isn't ready to use because the dedicated IP warm-up process is ongoing.
DONE --- The dedicated IP warm-up process is complete, and the IP address is ready to use.

nested_items.name: WarmupPercentage
nested_items.description: Indicates how complete the dedicated IP warm-up process is. When this value equals 1, the address has completed the warm-up process and is ready for use.

nested_items.name: PoolName
nested_items.description: The name of the dedicated IP pool that the IP address is associated with.
